SIMPLE: impotency
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Impotency
<hw>Im"po*ten*cy</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>impotenia</ets>
inability, poverty, lack of moderation. See <er>Impotent</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or condition of being impotent; lack of
strength or power, animal, intellectual, or moral; weakness; feebleness;
inability; imbecility.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Some were poor by <qex>impotency</qex> of nature; as young
fatherless children, old decrepit persons, idiots, and cripples.</q>
<rj><qau>Hayward.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>O, <qex>impotence</qex> of mind in body strong!</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Lack of self-restraint or self-control.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Law & Med.)</fld> <def>Lack of procreative power;
inability to copulate, or beget children; also, sometimes, sterility;
barrenness;</def> <specif>specifically, in males:</specif> <def>the
inability to achieve or sustain a penile erection; erectile
dysfunction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>impregnated</ent>⟦br⟧
